<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>suck</title>
  <style>
    @font-face {
      font-family: "BubbleGums";
      src: url("BUBBLEGUMS.TTF");
      font-weight: normal;
      font-style: normal;
    }

    @font-face {
      font-family: "HonobonoPop";
      src: url("HonobonoPopTTF-Regular.TTF");
      font-weight: normal;
      font-style: normal;
    }

    body {
      font-family: BubbleGums, Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
      text-align: center;
    }

    a {
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: black;
      text-shadow: #00FF00 1px 1px;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-shadow: #FF0000 1px 1px;
    }

    li {
      list-style-type: none;
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    var user = {
      name: JSON.stringify(<%= user.name %>),
      fbid: <%= user.fbid %>
    }
  </script>
</head>

<body>
  <h1>suck</h1>
  <p>This game sucks.</p>

  <% if (user.name) { %>
  <p>Welcome back, <%- user.name %></p>
  <p>Your biggest suck was <%- user.top_score %></p>

  <div id="paymentSection">
    <form id="purchaseForm">
      <% if (!user.hasSavedPin) { %>
      <input type="number" id="pinInput" placeholder="Enter PIN" required style="font-family: BubbleGums; font-size: 1em; padding: 5px; margin: 5px;">
      <br>
      <label style="margin: 10px;">
        <input type="checkbox" id="savePinCheck"> Save PIN for quick rebuy
      </label>
      <br>
      <% } %>
      <button type="submit" style="text-shadow: #00FF00 1px 1px; color: black; font-family: BubbleGums; font-size: 1em; padding: 10px 20px; cursor: pointer; margin: 10px;">Pay 25 Digipogs & Play</button>
    </form>
  </div>
  <% } else { %>
  <p><a href="/login">Log in to play</a></p>
  <% } %>
  <h2>What is suck?</h2>
  <p>suck is basically agar.io, except it sucks.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      You are a suck.
    </li>
    <li>
      Suck up smaller sucks to become bigger suck.
    </li>
    <li>
      Don't get sucked.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>There are <b><%- numPlayers %></b> sucks currently sucking.</p>
  <h3>The Best Suck</h3>
  <p><b><%- game.top_name %></b> was the biggest suck of all time. ( <b><%- game.top_score %></b> )</p>
  <p>People have attempted to be the biggest suck <b><%- game.hits_game %></b> times.</p>
  <p><b><%- game.hits_home %></b> people have read this sentence.</p>

  <% if (user.name) { %>
  <script>
    // Handle purchase form submission
    const hasSavedPin = <%= user.hasSavedPin ? 'true' : 'false' %>;
    
    document.getElementById('purchaseForm').addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();

      const submitBtn = e.target.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
      const originalText = submitBtn.textContent;
      
      submitBtn.textContent = 'Processing...';
      submitBtn.disabled = true;

      try {
        let body;
        if (hasSavedPin) {
          body = JSON.stringify({ useSaved: true });
        } else {
          const pin = parseInt(document.getElementById('pinInput').value);
          const savePIN = document.getElementById('savePinCheck').checked;
          body = JSON.stringify({ pin, savePIN });
        }

        const response = await fetch('/purchase', {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: {
            'Content-Type': 'application/json'
          },
          body: body
        });

        const result = await response.json();

        if (result.success) {
          submitBtn.textContent = 'Success! Loading game...';
          window.location.href = '/game';
        } else {
          submitBtn.textContent = result.message;
          submitBtn.style.backgroundColor = '#FF0000';
          setTimeout(() => {
            submitBtn.textContent = originalText;
            submitBtn.style.backgroundColor = '';
            submitBtn.disabled = false;
          }, 3000);
        }
      } catch (error) {
        submitBtn.textContent = 'Error! Try again';
        submitBtn.style.backgroundColor = '#FF0000';
        setTimeout(() => {
          submitBtn.textContent = originalText;
          submitBtn.style.backgroundColor = '';
          submitBtn.disabled = false;
        }, 3000);
      }
    });
  </script>
  <% } %>
</body>

</html>